description: Try our easy to follow Moist Choc-Chip Banana Cake recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Moist Choc-Chip Banana Cake Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 180Â°C. Grease and line a 20 x 10 x 7cm (7-cup capacity) deep loaf tin with baking paper.
Beat butter and sugar together with electric beaters until pale and creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until just combined. Add vanilla and beat until combined.

Add flour, bicarbonate of soda and milk alternatively. Stir in mashed banana and 3/4 of choc chips and walnuts, if using. Stir until combined. Pour mixture into prepared pan, smooth top and sprinkle with remaining choc chips. Bake for 45 minutes or until a skewer comes out clean when inserted into centre of the cake. Stand for 10 minutes before turning out onto a wire rack to cool. Slice and serve.
